rain\n-Jyou want relief\u2014want it fast I Another\ndisturbance may be mild bladder irritation\nfollowing wrong food and drink\u2014often set\nting up a restless uncomfortable feeling.\nDoan's Pills work fast in 8 separate\nways I 1. by speedy pain-relieving action to\nease torment of nagging backache, head\naches, muscular aches and pains. 2. by\nsoothing effect on bladder irritation. 3: by\nmild diuretic action tending to increase\noutput of the IB miles of kidney tubes.\nEnjoy a good night's sleep and the\nsame happy relief millions have for over\n60 years. New large size saves money.\nGet Doan's Pills today I\nWILMER T. DERICKSON CO.\nDover, Delaware\n-EXCLUSIVE BUYERS OF\nLIVE POULTRY\nFowl and Roosters\u2014(No Broilers) for\nRICHARDSON AND ROBBINS CO.\nPHONE: DOVER 4781\n1 -6-eow\ne\nCome In and see our INTERNATIONAL Truck\nPOWR-LOK Test\"!\nw\n\"A\nI l:\nmot\n\u25a0Mj\nSS?##\n-v\nM\nft\ngl;:#;\n\n4\u00bb.\n\u25a0m\n:-x\n\u25a0y\nlili\n\nx;x:\nw\nHi\n\nx\n\n\u25a0m\n\u00caT\n\u2022x\ni\ny\nf\n>X\nI\n\n.vv.v.y.\nJ\nX\n\u00c4\n\ni\n\n1\n\nI\nA\nIQW\ns\nW\n\n,1\n\nI\ni\n\nI l\nm\nf*\nIT\nm\n\u25a0i V\n\nmm\n:|:x\nr*\nV\nL,\nv.\nIt's next b\u00e7st to having traction power\nand the cost is so lowl\n\non all four wheels\nNOW! Only s 35\n00\nPOWR-LOK is an ingenious new\ndiiTerential that gives power to the\nrear wheel that has the most traction.\nWith POWR-LOK you pull\nthrough mud holes, loose sand, other\nslippery places that would normally\nstop a truck with standard differ\nential.\nSo don't spin your wheels. Be sure\nyour next truck is an International\nwith POW'R-LOK differential. Come\nin and see our convincing test, first\nchance you get.\nFactory >-Installed or a\nNaw INTERNATIONAL\nTruck. Fadaral and\nlocal taxaa additional.\n\nHow POWR-LOK Works\nWith a convsntional differential,\npower goes to the wheel with the\nfeait traction. This retvlts in a lost\nof power\u2014and you're stuck. 8ut\nwith POWR-LOK, power goes to\nthe wheel with the most '.loction.\nSo long as either wheel can catch\nhold, you keep moving.\nINTERNATIONAL TRUCKS cost least to ownl\nBROWN P. THAWLEY, Inc.\nPhone Milford 8059\nMilford, Delaware\nRehoboth Cut-Off\nGranville Shockley and son Lio\nnel, Richard and John and Ray\nmond Davis all attended the Har\nrisburg Fair last week.\nGus Hoger is still very sick at\nhis home near the dyke.\nMonday night callers on Mr. and\nMrs. James E. Mills were Airman\nand Mrs. Gene Keene and son and\nSergeant and Mrs. Joe Davis and\nson.\nSeveral ladies attended the\nFarm Bureau dinner in the Dover\nHotel on Wednesday.\n\"Wit and wisdom are born with\na man.\"\nEugene Mills met.with a pain\nful accident on Saturday when a\nbull knocked down .a steel pole in\nthe stable and hit him on the head.\nHe was rushed to the Milford Me\nmorial Hospital where they found\nhe had a fractured skull. At pres\nent he is doing very nicely. We\nhope he has a speedy recovery with\nno after effects.\n\"He that lives upon hopes will\ndie fasting.\"\nMr. and Mrs. Brownlow Morris\nwere Friday night callers on Mr.\nand Mrs. Eugene Mills.\nLittle Susan Mills is staying with\nher cousins, Beverly and Brenda\nDonovan. Eugene is staying with\nhis grandparents, Mr. and Mrs,\nJames D. Mills and Faye and Paul\nare staying with their aunt, Mrs.\nAnna Lee Strahle. This gives their\nmother Fannie Mae more time to\nspend In the hospital as her mo\nther and husband are both there.\nLittle Barbara Gayle Ashton is\nspending some time with her\ngrandparents, Mr. and Mrs. Lu\ncius Webb.\nLittle Nancy Hayes has been\nshut in sick for the past couple\nof weeks. Nancy is the second\ndaughter of Mr. and Mrs. John\nHayes.\nDare to be a Daniel,\nDare to stand alone;\nDare to have a purpose firm,\nDare to make it known.\nThomas Mills, 3rd, spent the\nweek-end with his grandparents,\nMr. and Mrs. Thomas Mills, Sr.\nMrs. Lydia' Mills' mother, Mrs.\nAlice Shepard is in the Milford\nMemorial Hospital quite ill. We\nwish her a speedy recovery.\nMrs. Melinda Mills and son\nThomas Mills, Sr., and Mr. and\nMrs. Miles Mills visited Mrs. Min\nnie Camper in Frederica on Tues\nday. Mrs. Camper Is recovering\nfrom a broken hip.\n\"If the Lord is with me how\ndare I fear.\nMrs. Anna Carroll, Mrs. Edith\nReed and Mrs. Hilda Shockley\nspent Friday shopping in Wilming\nton. On their return home they\nstopped at the Calvary Methodist\nChurch where the Sunshine Class\nwas meeting and enjoyed the pic\ntures shown by Mrs. Elizabeth\nWard that were taken in Hawaii.\nFor what shall it profit a man\nif he shall gain the whole world\nand Ic^.e his own soul?\u2014Mark 8:36.\n\nRead The Classified Ads\nComing Events\nFor Farm Folk\nJanuary 27\u2014Delaware Swine Pro\nducers Meeting, Agricultural Sub\nstation, Georgetown, Delaware,\n7:30 p. m.\nJanuary 27\u2014New Castle Co.,\nLeader Training Mtg., Room 032,\nAgricultural Hall, Newark, 1:00\n3:00 p. m.\nJanuary 27\u2014Officers' Training\nMeeting, Agricultural Hall, New\nark. 8:00 p. m.\nJanuary 30\u2014Leader Training\nMeeting, Capital Grange Hall,\nDover, 10:00 a. m.-3:00 p. m. \"Easy\nPreparations of Seafoods\".\nJanuary 30*\u2014Area Poultry Meet\ning, ESPGB Selbyville, 8:00 n. m.\nFebruary 5\u2014Recreation Leader\nship Training Meeting, Midland\nGrange Hall, Georgetown, 7:30 p. m.\nFebruary 6\u2014Sussex Leader Train\ning Meeting, Grange Hall, George\ntown, 10:00 a. m.-3;00 p. m. \"Sea\nfoods\".\nFebruary 11-12-13\u2014Annual Farm\nand Home Week, University of\nDelaware School of Agriculture,\nNewark.\nFebruary 11\u2014Winter Meeting of\nNortheast Farm Managers and Ru\nral Appraisers, Agricultural Hall,\nNewark.\nFebruary 12\u2014Tour of Delaware\nBroiler Industry by members of\nthe Society of Northeast Farm\nManagers and Rural Appraisers.\nFebruary 18\u20144-H Junior Council\nMeeting, Agricultural Center,\nGeorgetown, 7:30 p. m.\nFebruary 18\u2014Sussex Group Meet\ning No. 1\u2014Coolspring Group Hall,\nHarbeson, 1:30 p. m., \"Better Un\nderstanding of People\"; Group No.\n2\u2014Greenwood Fire Hall, Green\nwood, 7:30 p. m.\nFebruary 19\u2014Sussex Group Meet\ning No. 3\u2014St. George's Community\nHall, Bacons, 1:30 p. m.; Group No.\n4 Georgetown High School,\nGeorgetown, 7:30 p. m.\nFebruary 26\u2014New Castle Co.\nLeader Training Meeting, Trinity\nMethodist Church, Wilmington,\n10:00 a. m.-12:00 noon.\nFebruary 27\u2014New Castle Co.\nLeader Training Meeting, Room\n032, Agricultural Hall, Newark,\n1:00-3:00 p. m.\nFebruary 28-March 1\u2014Eastern\nStates Farmers' Exchange Annual\nAnnual Meeting, Springfield, Mass.\nMarch 12\u2014Regional Poultry Meet\ning, (all-day)), Salisbury, Md.\nMarch 27\u2014DPIA Annual Ban\nquet, Caesar Rodney School, 6:30\np. m.\nMarch 30-J1\u2014Food Retailers'\nShort Course, University of Dela\nware, Newark, Delaware.\nApril 10-11-12\u2014Middle Atlantic\nGrange Lecturers' Conference, Ho\ntel Rodney. Wilmington, Delaware.\nWDEL FARM AND HOME HOUR\n12:30-12:45 Monday Saturday,\n1150 K. C.\nJanuary 27\u2014Si McMenry, Exten\nsion Poultryman.\nJanuary 28\u2014Bob Bull, Agent in\nMarketing.\nJanuary 29\u2014Chemistry of Fruit\nRipening Woodmansee.\nJanuary 30\u2014Bill Mitchell, Ass't.\nProf, of Agronomy.\nJanuary 31\u2014Marjorie Wormeck,\nExtension Nutrition specialist.\nFebruary 1\u2014Maurice Field, 4-H\nClub Agent.\nSLOW DRIVER\nCHATHAM, Ont. (\u00c6*) A 17\nyear-old youth appeared in court\nhere on a seldom-heard charge\u2014\ndriving at an unnecessarily slow\nspeed. The case was adjourned.\n-\u25a0-Sc\nJ\nFREDERICA\nMrs. Emma Dolan\nPhone Frederica 6-6481\nTrinity Methodist Church\nRev. Jacob C. Hanby, Pastor\nPhone Frederica 5-6388\nOrganist, Dorothy Warren\nChurch School at 9:45 a. m.\nJohn H. Woodrow, superintendent.\nMorning Worship at 11 a. m.\nMYF at 7 p. m.'\nThe Methodist Youth Fellowship\nmet at 7 p. m. last Sunday with\nEbbie Warren, leader. There was\na special program about hymns and\nstories and why they were written.\nThe heart of our teaching is ev\ner before us; an anchorage in the\nChristian faith learning to live\nas a child of God; a sense of com\nmitment to and companionship\nwith Jesus should ever be our\nguide of life. If you, or a member\nof your family are not attending\nSunday School or the worship ser\nvices and you believe in them, why\nnot give special invitation to at\ntend. Give God the best you have\nin service. He gave H s Son for\nyou.\nA meeting of the Commission on\nEvangelism met Sunday afternoon\nat 4 o'clock. Mrs. Dorothy Rob\nbins was the chairman.\nA zone meeting of the Dover Dis\ntrict Woman's Society of Chris\ntian Service was held here in\nchurch on Tuesday evening at 7:30\no'clock. Mrs. Dorothy Reynolds,\nSardis Church, had charge of the\ndevotions. All of the women of\nthe church were invited.\nGood news from the WSCS. At\nthe last meeting the society receiv\ned four new members.\nOur prayers go out to Mrs. Irene\nSpurry and Wilson Conley for a\nspeedy recovery, also to David Rob\nbins and family in their sorrow.\nErnest C Macklin\nINSURANCE\nAuto Fire Life\n208 Truitt Avenue\nPHONE 5722\nMILFORD, DEL.\nGet Maximum vhT\nYields\nI\n\n\nf\ni\nJ\n\nsouthern)\nE Sjt\n~nnrrn iTrrjg 5\nr f\nk\n\nv\n7\nV\n\u00cf\n\u25a0I\nV\nu\n\nVj*\n4\nA\nV\nt\nW\u00ef\nMUH SHIES COOPE\nip.iP\nPPPPP\n\u00dc\u00c4\n\nX\n\nm\n\u00dc\nm\nm\nX\n\u2022\u2022XX.'\nv\nW\n\n\u00c4\nX\nf X:\nX x\n\nx\nW\n\nm\n\n\nV\nm\n\nX\n\nXX\nxX\nmm\n:x;\nmm#.\nx\nmnm. T:\nf y.V- y Vi (c.\n'M\n\n\nx-^\n:iS\n\u2022XX\nX.\n\n\nw\nxX\n\nM\nm\nft:\nWm.. \u00e0\nmmm\nI\nX\nwmm\n'.'\u25a0.ft\n\u2022X'X\n\np M\n'-ft\nft.\nA\n\nmy.\n\u25a0ft\n\nft-.\nmi\n\nmm-\n\n\n\u2022X\nORDEk NOW\nfor 1958\nSpring\nDelivery\n\n'\u25a0if'-'\nr\nn\n\nx\nv\nand have your seeds when you need them\nSee Your Local Southern States Cooperative Service Agency\nMOW\nma\nThe pastor is asking every one\nto register today.\nYou have a home. You have a\nschool. Do you have a church?\nMr. and Mrs. Clarence Jester en\ntertained at a family dinner on Fri\nday evening in honor, of Mr. Jes\nter's mother, Mrs. Elizabeth Jes\nter. Present besides the three Jes\nters were their children, Mrs. John\nWilson, Mr. and Mrs. C. Donovan\nand son, Mr. and Mrs. C. Rentz, Jr.,\nand Robert Jester. Mrs. Jebter re\nceived some very lovely gifts.\nMr. and Mrs. Clarence Jester and\ndaughter, Mrs. John Wilson spent\nSt nday with Mr.. and Mrs. Rich\nard Wilson in New Jersey.\nMarjorie Hudson of Bowers\nspent the week-end with Sarah\nJane Matlack.\nOur town was shocked over the\naccident to Mrs. Seretha Beebe last\nThursday. Mrs. Beebe is a very\nactive lady, in our church work and\npresident of Lie WSCS, and a\nmember of the Ladies' Auxiliary\nat the Frederica Fire Hall. She\nwas busy working for the supper\nat the fire house on Thursday eve\nning. Her many friends and neigh\nbors wish her a speedy recovery.\nMrs. Evelyn Sharp spent Satur\nday with her daughter, Mr. and\nMrs. Cooper Bostic in Ellendale.\nMrs. Mary Boone, Mr. and Mrs.\nS. Gottorf. all of Dover, visited\nMrs. E. Jestei on Sunday after\nnoon.\nThere are many of our town folk\nand children on the sick list. Little\nJo Ann Thomas was out of school\nlast week, 111. Mr. and Mrs. George\nTV ANTENNAS\nINSTALLED REPAIRED MOVED\nFREE ESTIMATES CALL ANY TIME\nSERVICE CALLS $3.50\nMilford Harrington Road\nWe Service AU Makes Television Sets\nDELMOR T-V COMPANY\nFRANKLIN CtlRREY\nIF NO ANSWER CALL HARRINGTON 8640 12-16-tf\n\nMIN.\nMilford, Del.\nPhone 8534\nDolan, Mrs. Susan Kemp, Mrs.\nMargaret Carlisle, Mr. and Mrs.\nNutter Marvel. To these and any\nothers in town who aie ilf, we\nwish a speedy recovery; also Wil\nliam Harper.\nMr. and Mrs. Merton Betts of\nnear Newark spent Sunday with\nhis parents, Mr. and Mrs. Louder\nBetts and family.\nMrs. Ann Oliver and daughter\nLinda of Dover visited with Mr.\nand Mrs. Charles E. Stubbs and\nfamily and Mr. and Mrs. Coverdale\nand family on Sunday. The Clif\nford Coverdales, children, Mr. and\nMrs. William Glanden and chil\ndren of Cape Charles, Va, spent\nSunday with their parents, Mr. and\nMrs. Jimmie Coverdale and sons\nof Mifford, were afternoon visit\nors.\nMr. and Mrs. C. E. Stubbs and\nfamily were Sunday dinner guests\nof her brother, Mr. anji Mrs. J.\nCoverdale of Milford.\nLois Ann Jester spent the week\nend with Johanna Lee Brewster\nand her parents, Staff Sergeant and\nMrs. Brewster of North Bowers.\nThey all enjoyed Saturday evening\nat the bowling alley in Dagsboro.\nHenry Lynch is a patient in\nthe Milford Memorial Hospital. He\nsuffered a heart attack on Thurs\ncay evening.\nMiss Carolyn Homey of Wil\nmington spent the week-end with\nMr. and Mrs. Drexel Coverdale and\nfamily.\nMrs. Oliver Boone attended the\nfuneral of her uncle, John Tim\nmons at Baltimore on Monday.\nT\nStaff Sergeant and Mrs. Gilbert\nHagin and children have returned\nhome after a trip south as far as\nFlorida.\nMrs. A. Lank was with her daugh\nter for a few days last week, Mrs.\nRowe Pleasanton, who was ill.\nMr. and Mrs. Rowe Pleasanton\nand daughters of Dover, were Sun\nday ditmer guests of her parents,\nMr. and Mrs. Arch Lank.\nMrs. Ralph Jester was a visitor\nJohn Darling is spending a few\ndays in Florida.\nMrs. Ella Walls of Collingswood,\nN. is staying with her sister,\nMrs. Nutter Marvel, while Mr. Mar\nvel is in the Milford Memorial Hos\npital.\non Saturday evening of Mr. and\nMrs. George Dolan.\n\nBrooklyn has a bigger population\nthan Manhattan. The count Is: Brook\nlyn, 2,731,000; Manhattan, 1,898,000.\nI\n\n\u00dcito\nEvery one's Reaching\nSWEETHEART BREAD\nWITH BUTTER ADDED\nAc,\n\nm\nX\n\nff\nBi\nA\none to five inches long, a 14-inch\ni pocket watch, a\nspring, two large\npieces of glass, a swivel and a\npart of a gear from a fishing reel.\ni pieces of wire of various lengths\nand thickness, plugs and several\ntravelers, which are metal objects\noff textile machines,\nSTRONG STOMACH\nSHJLBY, N. C. (\u00c6*) A cow\nof the Ora Mill farm herd died\nrecently. The mill dump is near\nthe pasture;\nFarm Superintendent Vetus\nQueen said a post-mortem disclos\ned the following in the cow's stom\nach\nThree razor blades, four nails\nchain from a\nclothes pin\n\nEver add crumbled crisply cook\ned bacon to the yolk stuffing for\ndevelied eggs?","height":"25335","width":"20418"}}
